## Web Search Results

**SQ10 — xtask skeleton convention check**

- **Canonical skeleton** (matklad/cargo-xtask, the de facto spec): root has `.cargo/config.toml`, root `Cargo.toml` declaring a workspace, sibling `xtask/` and `<main-crate>/` directories, each with their own `Cargo.toml` and `src/` — confirmed verbatim from the upstream README. Source: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask/blob/master/README.md
- **Cargo alias** is one line: `[alias] xtask = "run --package xtask --"` placed in `.cargo/config.toml`. The alias works from any subdirectory only when xtask is a workspace member. Source: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask/blob/master/README.md
- **Entry-point shape**: `xtask/src/main.rs` parses at least one positional arg (the task name) and dispatches to subcommand functions implemented in plain Rust. Tasks may shell out to `cargo` via the `CARGO` env var. Source: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask
- **Workspace vs single-crate**: matklad's own guidance is that xtask SHOULD be a workspace member — enables shared dep resolution and the simple alias. The non-workspace fallback (`run --manifest-path ./xtask/Cargo.toml --`) is documented but discouraged. Sources: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask/issues/8 and https://matklad.github.io/2021/08/22/large-rust-workspaces.html
- **Status of the pattern**: not officially blessed by the cargo team, but widely adopted — cargo itself uses xtasks; rust-analyzer ships an `xtask` crate documented at https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-analyzer/xtask/index.html. Source: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask
- **Subcommand catalog precedent (OpenVMM)** — uses xtask as a "swiss army knife" with subcommands like `clean`, `fmt`, `fuzz`, `install-git-hooks`; running bare `cargo xtask` prints the list. Suggests built-in `--help` discovery is the dominant convention. Source: https://openvmm.dev/guide/dev_guide/dev_tools/xtask.html
- **Helper crates exist** (optional, not canonical): `xtaskops` (jondot) and `xtasks` (sebastienrousseau) bundle reusable task primitives — coverage, ci, bloat-deps, powerset. Useful as reference for *what subcommands large packs ship* but they are not part of the convention. Sources: https://github.com/jondot/xtaskops and https://github.com/sebastienrousseau/xtasks
- **Security-task precedent**: searches did not surface a widely-cited "security xtask" template specifically; OpenVMM's `fuzz` subcommand is the closest documented example. No public Rust-project xtask is named as canonical for SAST verification. Source: https://openvmm.dev/guide/dev_guide/dev_tools/xtask.html
- **Cargo subcommand naming**: the convention is to expose all custom work under a single `xtask` binary with subcommands (`cargo xtask <name>`) rather than multiple `xtask-foo` aliases — explicitly recommended in matklad's spec. Source: https://github.com/matklad/cargo-xtask/blob/master/README.md

